cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new routing algorithm for capsule networks and applies it to two different domains: vision and language. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, since the first network achieves state-of-the-art accuracy on a visual recognition task, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a pretrained transformer, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper proposes a new algorithm for routing capsules, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
